trans-unit.source: Provides services for editing control templates at design time.
This class cannot be inherited.
The <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.TemplateEditingService> class is obsolete.
Expose templates through the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner.TemplateGroups%2A> property of a control designer.

Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.UI.Design.TemplateEditingService"></xref> class with the specified designer host.
The <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.TemplateEditingService> class is obsolete.
Expose templates through the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner.TemplateGroups%2A> property of a control designer.

An <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.IDesignerHost"></xref> implementation, used to access components at design time.

The name of the editing frame that will be displayed on the frame.

Typically, this is the same as the <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.DesignerVerb.Text"></xref> used as the menu text for the <xref href="System.Web.UI.Design.TemplateEditingVerb"></xref> that is invoked to create the frame.

The <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.TemplateEditingService> class is obsolete.

Use the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.TemplatedEditableDesignerRegion.TemplateDefinition%2A> property of the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.TemplatedEditableDesignerRegion> class for equivalent design-time functionality.
The <xref href="System.Web.UI.Control"></xref> for which to get the name of the parent template.
The name of the parent template.
Gets a value that indicates whether the service supports nested template editing.
The <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.TemplateEditingService> class is obsolete.
Expose templates through the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner.TemplateGroups%2A> property of a control designer.

The design host creates a <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.TemplatedEditableDesignerRegion> object for each <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.TemplateDefinition> in each <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.TemplateGroup> that is defined for a control designer.

The <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.TemplateEditingService.SupportsNestedTemplateEditing%2A> property indicates whether a template editor can be invoked from a component of a parent template editor's templated control.
This is called nested template editing, because a template editor is invoked for a component of a control for which a template editor is already operating.
`true` if the service supports nested template editing; otherwise, `false`.
